WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.480
Dr. These are my financial disclosures. So, as we heard a few minutes ago, so,

00:00:06.480 --> 00:00:13.200
loncoxtrexamab/tesirine is an antibody drug conjugate consisting of CD19-directed monoclonal

00:00:13.200 --> 00:00:19.760
antibody in combination with PBD dimer, which is an active drug, which is what causes majority of

00:00:19.760 --> 00:00:26.320
the anti-lymphoma activities. So, this is a LOTIS 5 trial design. This was a phase 3 confirmatory

00:00:26.320 --> 00:00:32.320
trial for loncoxtrexamab/tesirine. The study involved a non-randomized safety running phase

00:00:32.320 --> 00:00:37.920
in which 20 patients were enrolled. Patients received loncoxtrexamab/tesirine 0.15 milligram

00:00:37.920 --> 00:00:42.720
per kilogram in combination with rituximab every three weeks for the first two cycles.

00:00:42.720 --> 00:00:48.960
Subsequently, the dose of loncoxtrexamab/tesirine was reduced to 0.075 milligram per kilogram with

00:00:48.960 --> 00:00:56.080
rituximab every three weeks. Total number of cycles were offered were eight for all patients.

00:00:56.320 --> 00:01:01.760
After the safety running, patients were randomized to, in one-to-one fashion,

00:01:01.760 --> 00:01:07.520
to loncoxtrexamab with rituximab for a total of eight cycles versus R-Gemox for a total of eight

00:01:07.520 --> 00:01:13.760
cycles. The primary endpoint is progression-free survival by independent central review.

00:01:13.760 --> 00:01:19.600
The key exclusion criteria include patients with relapsed diffuse-dot B-cell lymphoma after one

00:01:19.600 --> 00:01:24.480
prior line of therapies and those with measurable disease. Patients should not be a candidate for

00:01:24.480 --> 00:01:29.280
stem cell transplant based on performance status, advanced age, or any other significant

00:01:29.280 --> 00:01:35.600
comorbidities per the investigation descriptions. So, for the safety running, 20 patients were

00:01:35.600 --> 00:01:40.560
enrolled, and this data represents the safety running period. The randomization results are

00:01:40.560 --> 00:01:48.880
awaiting. So, out of 20 patients, majority, almost half of the patients had advanced DLBCL.

00:01:51.360 --> 00:01:53.680
The majority of the patients has relapsed disease.

00:01:54.480 --> 00:02:00.400
As you can see, out of 20 patients, median number of loncoxtrexamab and rituximab cycles

00:02:00.400 --> 00:02:06.720
were administered were five. One-third of patients only could finish all the eight cycles of treatment

00:02:06.720 --> 00:02:10.400
and 20 percent of patients withdrew from treatment due to adverse events.

00:02:11.520 --> 00:02:17.360
Now, in terms of side effect or safety profile, grade three treatment emergent adverse events were

00:02:17.360 --> 00:02:22.400
reported in 55 percent of patients. Serious adverse events were reported in approximately

00:02:22.400 --> 00:02:24.320
half of the patients. And 40 percent of patients were reported in 55 percent of patients. And 40

00:02:24.320 --> 00:02:29.280
percent of patients had steady drug withdrawal due to treatment emergent adverse events.

00:02:30.480 --> 00:02:36.640
Now, in terms of efficacy results among 20 patients, overall response rates were 80 percent

00:02:36.640 --> 00:02:40.480
and complete response rate was 50 percent. Just to give the perspective,

00:02:40.480 --> 00:02:47.920
single-agent loncoxtrexamab in LOTUS2 had a CR rate of 24 percent and response rates were 50

00:02:47.920 --> 00:02:52.400
percent. So, this was significantly higher than what we have observed in third-line settings.

00:02:52.400 --> 00:02:57.680
Now, in terms of side effect, grade four treatment emergent adverse events were reported in 55 percent

00:02:57.680 --> 00:03:03.440
of patients. Median duration of response was eight months. And for among patients who achieved CR and

00:03:03.440 --> 00:03:10.080
MRD negative, there were 50 percent of patients and half of the patients had MRD negative at the

00:03:10.080 --> 00:03:15.680
end of treatment. These were the biomarker results. On the left side of this slide shows essentially

00:03:15.680 --> 00:03:22.240
CD19 scoring pattern and the best overall response. Essentially, it shows that the response rates,

00:03:22.240 --> 00:03:26.000
as you can see, were 40 percent higher than what we have observed. So, this shows that the response

00:03:26.000 --> 00:03:30.080
rates, as you can see, were 50 percent higher than what we have observed. And this shows that the

00:03:30.080 --> 00:03:33.200
response rates, as you can see, were 50 percent higher than what we have observed. And the best

00:03:33.200 --> 00:03:36.560
overall response rates, as you can see, were 50 percent higher than what we have observed. And the

00:03:36.560 --> 00:03:39.120
best overall response rates, as you can see, were 50 percent higher than what we have observed. And

